<h1><center>HANDWRITING SECTION</center></h1>
<p>In order to investigate and unearth the mysteries of the crime like illegal possession of land or 
property, misappropriation of wealth, threatening someone or realization of ransom by anonymous letters,
 fraudulence, fleecing money from bank or any other financial institutions, forgeries as well as to
  bring the criminals under the purview of law and finally help out the courts to punish them are the 
  core responsibilities of Handwriting/ Document Analysis Section of Criminal Investigation Department 
 (CID). It provides expert opinions by restoring chemically or physically erased documents and
 indentations, detects any sort of addition or segregation in the documents, ascertains the 
 genuineness of documents having special security features, compares two or more seal impressions to 
 detect their genuineness, recognizes genuine and forged signature or writing and deciphers obliterated signature
 or writing. In a year the section analyzes documents of 1,300 to 1,500 cases containing 58,000 to
 60,000 exhibits on an average.</p>


